            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-09-05T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-09-05T10:00:00-05:00" n="458" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d458">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">824.6352/9–545: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">La Paz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-09-05T11:00:00-04:00">September 5, 1945—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 5:49 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>921. Dept’s A–294, August 28.<note n="78" xml:id="d458fn78">Not printed.</note>
                    Nothing has come to Embassy’s attention bearing out statement that adequate
                    steps taken for protection security American citizens. On contrary reports from
                    Quechisla–Oploca area situation worse and strike entailing danger to Americans
                    certain before year’s end. Embassy asking American company managers to report
                    carefully what steps taken to protect and whether situation improved. Their
                    reaction will be forwarded Dept. but above submitted for its consideration in
                    tin negotiations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thurston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
